[[File:Final ISO Red Square.png|thumb|150px|ISO logo]] '''ISO 20815''' is the [[International Organisation for Standardisation]] (ISO) standard for production assurance and reliability management in the [[petroleum]], [[Petrochemical industry|petrochemical]] and [[natural gas]] industries.<ref name=standard>[https://www.iso.org/standard/39744.html ISO 20815:2008: Petroleum, petrochemical and natural gas industries - Production assurance and reliability management], accessed 11 March 2018</ref>
The 2008 version of the standard was last reviewed and confirmed in 2012.<ref name=standard /> It is due to be replaced by ISO/DIS 20815, a new standard currently under development.<ref>[https://www.iso.org/standard/69983.html ISO/DIS 20815: Petroleum, petrochemical and natural gas industries - Production assurance and reliability management], accessed 11 March 2018</ref>
The division of the [[oil and gas industry]] into [[Upstream (petroleum industry)|upstream]], [[Midstream (petroleum industry)|midstream]] and [[Downstream (petroleum industry)|downstream]] sectors is referred to in the standard.
