{{Refimprove|date=June 2017}} {{Use dmy dates|date=January 2018}} {{Infobox television | show_name = Money for Nothing | image = | image_upright = | image_size = | image_alt = | caption = | show_name_2 = | genre = | creator = | developer = | director = | creative_director = | presenter = {{unbulleted list|Sarah Moore|Jay Blades|Ethan-James Osborne}} | starring = | narrated = [[Arthur Smith (comedian)|Arthur Smith]] | theme_music_composer = | opentheme = | endtheme = | composer = | country = United Kingdom | language = English | num_series = 4 | num_episodes = 100 | list_episodes = | executive_producer = | producer = | cinematography = | editor = <!-- Film editors --> | camera = <!-- Either Single-camera or Multi-camera --> | runtime = 44 minutes | company = <!-- Production companies only --> | distributor = | budget = | network = [[BBC One]] | picture_format = | audio_format = | first_aired = {{Start date|2015|09|07|df=y}} | last_aired = present | preceded_by = | followed_by = | related = ''Celebrity Money for Nothing'' <!-- To be used only for remakes, spin-offs, and adaptations --> | website = <!-- Remove or comment out this parameter line completely if URL exists on or is moved to Wikidata --> | production_website = }}
'''''Money For Nothing''''' is a British television programme hosted by Sarah Moore, Jay Blades and Ethan-James Osborne that airs on [[BBC]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvkev.co.uk/content/money-nothing-show-was-unsalvageable|title=Money For Nothing: this show was unsalvageable|author=Kevin O'Sullivan|publisher= tvkev.co.uk|date=20 July 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170903073829/http://www.tvkev.co.uk/content/money-nothing-show-was-unsalvageable|archivedate = 3 September 2017|accessdate=3 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b077nzdc|title=Money for Nothing - BBC One|website=BBC|accessdate=22 August 2017}}</ref>
==Format== The premise of the programme is to take items that other people have disposed of and which the presenter rescues from council refuse collection sites. With the help of a designer they are turned into desirable items, which are then sold. Any profit made is then returned to the individual(s) who disposed of the item originally. The show voice-over is provided by comedian and writer [[Arthur Smith (comedian)|Arthur Smith]]. ''Celebrity Money for Nothing'' is a related program.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.frielkeanfilms.com/?page=productions/celebrity-money-for-nothing|title=Celebrity Money for Nothing|website=Friel Kean Films|accessdate=10 September 2017}}</ref>
Regular designers and craftspeople include: Norman Wilkinson, Rupert Blanchard, Forge Creative (Josh Kennard & Oliver "Oli" Milne), Sarah Peterson, Neil Wragg, Ray Clarke, Daniel Health, Mark 'Horse' Philips, Bex Simon, The Rag and Bone Man, Guy Trench.
