{{Italic title}} {{Taxobox | name = ''Pyrrhulina'' | image = Lebiasinidae Pyrrhulina sp.jpg | image_caption = ''Pyrrhulina'' sp. | regnum = [[Animalia]] | phylum = [[Chordata]] | classis = [[Actinopterygii]] | ordo = [[Characiformes]] | familia = [[Lebiasinidae]] | genus = '''''Pyrrhulina''''' | genus_authority = [[Achille Valenciennes|Valenciennes]], 1846 | subdivision_ranks = [[Species]] | subdivision = See text | type_species = ''Pyrrhulina filamentosa'' | type_species_authority = Valenciennes, 1847 }} {{Wikispecies|Pyrrhulina}}
'''''Pyrrhulina''''' is a genus of freshwater fishes found in [[tropical]] [[South America]]. Several of these species are popular [[aquarium]] fish.<ref>{{cite encyclopedia | editor = [[Günther Sterba]] | encyclopedia = The Aquarist's Encyclopaedia |title= Pyrrhulina |year= 1983 |publisher= Edition Leipzig}}</ref>
''Pyrrhulina'' is closely related to ''[[Copeina]]'' and ''[[Copella (genus)|Copella]]'', although it is distinguished from the former by having only one row of teeth (''Copeina'' spp. have two). When the genus ''Copella'' was established, many species were removed from the genus ''Pyrrhulina'' and placed there, because differences in the [[Maxilla#In other animals|maxillary bones]] in the males had been detected. ''Copella'' species are slimmer and more elongated than those species that remained in the genus ''Pyrrhulina''.
==Species== The 18 currently recognized species in this genus are:<ref>{{FishBase genus | genus = Pyrrhulina| month = April| year = 2013}}</ref><ref name=NettoFerreira2013/> * ''[[Pyrrhulina australis]]'' <small>[[Carl H. Eigenmann|C. H. Eigenmann]] & [[Clarence Hamilton Kennedy|C. H. Kennedy]], 1903</small> * ''[[Pyrrhulina beni]]'' <small>[[Nathan Everett Pearson|N. E. Pearson]], 1924</small> * ''[[Pyrrhulina brevis]]'' <small>[[Franz Steindachner|Steindachner]], 1876</small> * ''[[Pyrrhulina eleanorae]]'' <small>[[Henry Weed Fowler|Fowler]], 1940</small> * ''[[Pyrrhulina elongata]]'' <small>[[Axel Zarske|Zarske]] & [[Jacques Géry|Géry]], 2001</small> * ''[[Pyrrhulina filamentosa]]'' <small>[[Achille Valenciennes|Valenciennes]], 1847</small> * ''[[Pyrrhulina laeta]]'' <small>([[Edward Drinker Cope|Cope]], 1872)</small> (halfbanded pyrrhulina) * ''[[Pyrrhulina lugubris]]'' <small>C. H. Eigenmann, 1922</small> * ''[[Pyrrhulina marilynae]]'' <small>[[André Luiz Netto-Ferreira|Netto-Ferreira]] & [[Manoela Maria Ferreira Marinho|Marinho]], 2013</small><ref name=NettoFerreira2013>Netto-Ferreira, A.L. & Marinho, M.M.F. (2013): New species of ''Pyrrhulina'' (Ostariophysi: Characiformes: Lebiasinidae) from the Brazilian Shield, with comments on a putative monophyletic group of species in the genus. ''Zootaxa, 3664 (3): 369–376.''</ref> * ''[[Pyrrhulina maxima]]'' <small>C. H. Eigenmann & [[Rosa Smith Eigenmann|R. S. Eigenmann]], 1889</small> * ''[[Pyrrhulina melanostoma]]'' <small>(Cope, 1870)</small> (blackmouth pyrrhulina) * ''[[Pyrrhulina obermulleri]]'' <small>[[George S. Myers|G. S. Myers]], 1926</small> * ''[[Pyrrhulina rachoviana]]'' <small>G. S. Myers, 1926</small> (fanning pyrrhulina) * ''[[Pyrrhulina semifasciata]]'' <small>Steindachner, 1876</small> * ''[[Pyrrhulina spilota]]'' <small>[[Stanley Howard Weitzman|S. H. Weitzman]], 1960</small> * ''[[Pyrrhulina stoli]]'' <small>[[Marinus Boeseman|Boeseman]], 1953</small> * ''[[Pyrrhulina vittata]]'' <small>[[Charles Tate Regan|Regan]], 1912</small> (banded pyrrhulina) * ''[[Pyrrhulina zigzag]]'' <small>Zarske & Géry, 1997</small>
